HEADWORD: Exostosis
<hw>Ex`os*to"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/; <?/ out + <?/ bone: cf. F <?/ <ets>exostose</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Any protuberance of a bone which is
not natural; an excrescence or morbid enlargement of a bone.</def>
<rj><au>Coxe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A knot formed upon or in the wood
of trees by disease.</def></p>

